    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-04-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-04-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="153" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d153">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1333.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-04-04">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 4, 1865</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have received your despatch of the 17th
                            ultimo, No. 900, informing me that the pirate Shenandoah had arrived at
                            Melbourne, and of the probable destination of that vessel after leaving
                            that port. I have communicated the information to the Secretary of the
                            Navy.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
